## Naming Conventions

### File names

- Unit/integration: `<source-file-name>.test.ts`
- E2E: `<workflow-name>.test.ts`

### Describe blocks

Use `describe` blocks to organize tests hierarchically. The outermost block names the system under test. Inner blocks name the specific behavior or endpoint.

```ts
describe('Asset API', () => {
  describe('GET /api/v1/assets', () => {
    it('returns a paginated list of active assets', async () => { ... })
    it('excludes soft-deleted assets from results', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 401 when user is not authenticated', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 403 when user lacks asset:read permission', async () => { ... })
    it('respects page and limit query parameters', async () => { ... })
    it('filters by department when departmentId query param is provided', async () => { ... })
  })

  describe('POST /api/v1/assets', () => {
    it('creates an asset with valid data and returns 201', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 422 when required fields are missing', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 422 when assetNumber exceeds maximum length', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 422 when acquisitionCost is negative', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 404 when departmentId does not exist', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 409 when assetNumber is already in use', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 401 when user is not authenticated', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 403 when user lacks asset:create permission', async () => { ... })
    it('writes an audit log entry on successful creation', async () => { ... })
    it('generates a QR code value on creation', async () => { ... })
  })
})
```

### Test descriptions

- Use full sentences that describe behavior: `'returns 422 when required fields are missing'`
- Do not use vague names: `'works correctly'`, `'handles error'`, `'test 1'`
- The test description should make sense as a standalone statement without reading the code

