## What to Test

### Every API endpoint must be tested for all of these cases:

| Case | Expected status | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Happy path (valid data, authorized) | 200 or 201 | Verify the response body shape |
| Format validation failure (TypeBox Step 1) | 422 | Test multiple invalid inputs |
| Business logic failure (Step 2) — not found | 404 | Test with non-existent IDs |
| Business logic failure (Step 2) — conflict | 409 | Test duplicate constraints |
| Unauthenticated request | 401 | No session cookie/token |
| Authenticated but insufficient permission | 403 | Use a user with a lower-privilege role |
| Rate limit exceeded | 429 | Test the 5/min auth and 20/min general limits |

### TypeBox validation schemas

Every TypeBox schema must have a dedicated unit test:

```ts
describe('insertAssetSchema', () => {
  it('accepts valid asset data', () => {
    const result = Value.Check(insertAssetSchema, validAssetData)
    expect(result).toBe(true)
  })

  it('rejects when assetName is empty string', () => {
    const result = Value.Check(insertAssetSchema, { ...validAssetData, assetName: '' })
    expect(result).toBe(false)
  })

  it('rejects when acquisitionCost is negative', () => {
    const result = Value.Check(insertAssetSchema, { ...validAssetData, acquisitionCost: -1 })
    expect(result).toBe(false)
  })

  it('rejects when departmentId is not a valid UUID format', () => {
    const result = Value.Check(insertAssetSchema, { ...validAssetData, departmentId: 'not-a-uuid' })
    expect(result).toBe(false)
  })
})
```

### RBAC permission checks

Every permission must be tested for both grant and denial:

```ts
describe('RBAC — asset:create permission', () => {
  it('grants access to gso_officer role', () => {
    expect(hasPermission('gso_officer', 'asset:create')).toBe(true)
  })

  it('grants access to super_admin role', () => {
    expect(hasPermission('super_admin', 'asset:create')).toBe(true)
  })

  it('denies access to auditor role', () => {
    expect(hasPermission('auditor', 'asset:create')).toBe(false)
  })

  it('denies access to mayor role', () => {
    expect(hasPermission('mayor', 'asset:create')).toBe(false)
  })

  it('denies access to inventory_team role', () => {
    expect(hasPermission('inventory_team', 'asset:create')).toBe(false)
  })
})
```

### Auth flows

```ts
describe('Authentication', () => {
  describe('Login', () => {
    it('returns a session cookie on successful login with valid credentials', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 401 on invalid password', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 401 on non-existent email', async () => { ... })
    it('logs the login attempt (success and failure) with IP and user agent', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 429 after 5 consecutive failed login attempts', async () => { ... })
  })

  describe('Session expiry', () => {
    it('invalidates a session after 8 hours of total age', async () => { ... })
    it('invalidates a session after 2 hours of inactivity', async () => { ... })
  })

  describe('User deactivation', () => {
    it('invalidates all active sessions immediately when a user is deactivated', async () => { ... })
    it('returns 401 on subsequent requests after session invalidation', async () => { ... })
  })
})
```

### Utility functions

```ts
describe('generateId', () => {
  it('returns a string', () => {
    expect(typeof generateId()).toBe('string')
  })

  it('returns a valid UUID v7 format', () => {
    const id = generateId()
    // UUID v7 format: xxxxxxxx-xxxx-7xxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
    expect(id).toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-7[0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-9a-f]{12}$/)
  })

  it('returns unique values on repeated calls', () => {
    const ids = new Set(Array.from({ length: 1000 }, () => generateId()))
    expect(ids.size).toBe(1000)
  })

  it('returns IDs that are sortable in chronological order', () => {
    const ids = [generateId(), generateId(), generateId()]
    const sorted = [...ids].sort()
    expect(sorted).toEqual(ids)
  })
})
```

