## E2E Tests with Playwright

E2E tests are in `tests/e2e/` and run with Playwright:

```bash
vp add -D playwright
vp add -D @playwright/test
```

### What E2E tests cover

E2E tests cover complete user workflows that span multiple API calls and UI interactions. They are slower than unit tests and run separately from the main test suite.

Critical E2E workflows that must have tests:

| Workflow | File |
|---|---|
| Admin invites user → user accepts → user logs in | `tests/e2e/auth.test.ts` |
| Session expires after 2h inactivity | `tests/e2e/auth.test.ts` |
| Admin deactivates user → sessions expire | `tests/e2e/auth.test.ts` |
| User creates asset with draft save and restore | `tests/e2e/asset-create.test.ts` |
| Asset is soft-deleted and excluded from lists | `tests/e2e/asset-lifecycle.test.ts` |
| Physical count marks asset missing → reconciliation issue created | `tests/e2e/physical-inventory.test.ts` |
| Completed project converts to PPE asset | `tests/e2e/project-conversion.test.ts` |
| Document uploaded via PaperlessNGX integration | `tests/e2e/documents.test.ts` |
| Rate limit triggered on login (5 req/min) | `tests/e2e/rate-limiting.test.ts` |
| Unauthorized user cannot access protected route | `tests/e2e/rbac.test.ts` |

### Running E2E tests

```bash
vp run test:e2e   # defined in package.json scripts
# or
vpx playwright test
```

E2E tests run against a local Docker Compose environment with all services running.

