## Coverage Expectations

While 100% coverage is not the goal, the following must be covered:

| Area | Minimum coverage expectation |
|---|---|
| RBAC permission logic | 100% — every role × permission combination |
| Auth flow (login, invite, session, deactivation) | 100% |
| TypeBox validation schemas | 100% of schema fields |
| API endpoints (happy path) | 100% of endpoints |
| API endpoints (error paths) | All documented error codes per endpoint |
| Database utilities (`generateId`, soft-delete helpers) | 100% |
| Business logic validation (Step 2 checks) | 100% of database cross-reference checks |

Run `vp test run --coverage` to generate a coverage report and check against these expectations.

---

## What Not to Test

Do not write tests for:

- **Drizzle ORM internals** — trust Drizzle to generate correct SQL; test your query logic, not Drizzle's engine
- **shadcn-svelte component rendering** — trust the UI library; test your business logic, not the button rendering
- **VitePlus/Vitest internals** — do not test the test runner
- **Third-party API behavior** (PaperlessNGX, Typesense, S3) — mock these in unit tests; test integration in E2E only
- **Trivial getters and setters** with no logic — these add noise with no signal

---

## Rules Summary

| Rule | Requirement |
|---|---|
| Test runner | `vp test` (Vitest) only — never `bun test` |
| Test location | Co-located with source files for unit/integration tests |
| E2E test location | `tests/e2e/` |
| Test structure | Arrange → Act → Assert |
| Independence | Each test sets up its own state via `beforeEach` |
| One behavior per test | Never test two unrelated behaviors in one `it()` block |
| New features | Must ship with tests in the same commit |
| Bug fixes | Must ship with a regression test in the same commit |
| Failing tests | Must not be skipped or commented out — fix them |
| Mock policy | Mock only external services; test against real DB |
| RBAC tests | Every role × permission pair must be explicitly tested |
| Auth tests | All auth flows must be tested including edge cases |
| TypeBox schemas | Every schema must have tests for valid and invalid inputs |

---

## For AI Agents Specifically

When an AI agent writes a new feature or endpoint, it must:

1. Write the tests in **the same commit** as the feature code — not in a follow-up commit
2. Test all documented error codes for every new API endpoint
3. Test RBAC denial for at least two roles that should not have access
4. Run `vp test` before committing and confirm all tests pass
5. Never write a test that simply asserts `true === true` to inflate coverage
6. Never skip a test with `.skip` or comment it out — if a test is failing, fix the underlying code
